<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,482,222,249]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,475,222,249]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[792,875,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head slightly convex, frons slightly concave. Marginal carina broad, narrowing anterior to 
<emphasis box="[993,1049,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">dsms</emphasis>
, deeply displaced and widened at osculum. Ventral anterior plate rounded, with concave anterior margin and straight lateral margins. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[212,296,329,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi wide, bulging. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular, lateral margins slightly concave. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[322,450,400,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–51" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[270,1302,193,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-17@23.[256,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 50–51. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 50, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 51, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825579/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 50–51</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation translucent; head nodi dark brown; mandibular framework, margins of antennal sockets, gular plate, proepimera, and metepisterna medium brown; sternal plates II–VI and subgenital plates pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1060]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,505,532]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[754,839,505,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–51" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[270,1302,193,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-17@23.[256,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 50–51. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 50, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 51, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825579/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
; sternite IV with 1 
<emphasis box="[1066,1096,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">sts</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme rounded proximally (
<figureCitation box="[390,474,541,568]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
), lateral margins concave. Proximal mesosome with slender antero-lateral extensions that almost reach lateral margins of basal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[734,865,576,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 53–54</figureCitation>
), proximal margin flat. Mesosomal lobes divergent distally. Distal margin of mesosome flat to slightly convex. Gonopore distally bifid, with slightly hooked anterolateral extensions. Dorsal fringe tilted slightly posteriorly, without thumb-like process. Chaetotaxy: 2 ventral 
<emphasis box="[1365,1437,647,672]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">gpmes</emphasis>
microsetae on each side of distal gonopore; 2 
<emphasis box="[678,743,681,707]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">lpmes</emphasis>
microsetae on each side on mesosomal lobes; 1 dorsal 
<emphasis box="[1379,1437,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ames</emphasis>
microseta on each side proximal to dorsal fringe. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[877,951,717,743]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[1017,1100,717,744]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1060]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,751,778]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[766,849,752,779]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–51" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[270,1302,193,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-17@23.[256,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 50–51. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 50, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 51, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825579" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825579/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
; abdominal segment VI with 1 
<emphasis box="[1199,1224,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Subgenital plate as in 
<figureCitation box="[350,431,787,814]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–56" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1389,205,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[179,1409,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 52–56. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) cinitemnina new species ex Edolisoma melas melas. 52, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 53, male genitalia, dorsal view. 54, male mesosome, ventral view. 55, male paramere, dorsal view. 56, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825581" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825581/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
, lateral margins sinuous, distal margin broadly flattened. Vulval margin concave medianly, with 2 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[388,432,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vms</emphasis>
and 1 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[696,730,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 4–7 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[1100,1137,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 2–3 
<emphasis box="[337,374,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vos</emphasis>
distal to 
<emphasis box="[478,512,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vss</emphasis>
, and about twice as long as 
<emphasis box="[828,872,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[1114,1198,857,884]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1060]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,893,919]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[820,873,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">cinis</emphasis>
” for “ash” and Greek “ 
<emphasis box="[1137,1226,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">temnein</emphasis>
” for “I cut”, referring to the ashy plumage of the host.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
